│ to the epilogue. In this scenario, the vectorizer correctly optimizes by not creating a    │
│ \"resume PHI\" node, as there's no value to resume from the main loop. The epilogue should │
│ simply start from the original loop's initial induction value.\n\n### 3. Root Cause        │
│ Analysis\n\nThe crash is caused by a disconnect between the logic for the main vector loop │
│ and the logic for the epilogue vectorization. The epilogue vectorization planning          │
│ function, `preparePlanForEpilogueVectorLoop`, unconditionally assumes that a resume PHI    │
│ node was created by the main vectorization pass. It searches for a specific PHI in the     │
